k's Vitest plugin, running in headless Chromium via\\n+   Playwright and loading Storybook project annotations, including a11y.\\n+\\n+Expose `storybook`, `storybook:build`, `storybook:test`, and\\n+`storybook:test:watch` scripts through `apps/web`.  The root test command is\\n+not broadened in this first tranche; browser tests remain an explicit gate\\n+until CI ownership is specified.\\n+\\n+The Storybook config must include `../../packages/ui/src/**/*.tsx` in\\n+`reactDocgenTypescriptOptions.include`.  In a workspace, docgen otherwise\\n+builds its TypeScript program from `apps/web` and can omit shared-component\\n+props.  During implementation, validate HMR after changing a UI component;\\n+if Vite does not follow the workspace symlink, configure the documented\\n+workspace-package change-detection remedy rather than copying source.\\n+\\n+## Story and test contract\\n+\\n+Every story must render an intentional, named component state.  Browser\\n+component tests come from Storybook smoke rendering plus `play` functions for\\n+user-visible behavior.  a11y failures fail the Storybook test project.\\n+\\n+| Component | States / interaction contract |\\n+| --- | --- |\\n+| Avatar | image, fallback, and stacked avatars; fallback remains named and usable. |\\n+| Button | standard variants and icon action; clicking invokes the supplied handler. Icon-only examples carry an explicit accessible name. |\\n+| Dropdown menu | open trigger, checkbox and radio state transitions, and submenu visibility. |\\n+| Switch | labelled toggle, default-checked, and disabled states; label activation and disabled non-interaction are asserted. |\\n+| Tabs | default and line variants; selecting a tab changes active state and visible panel. |\\n+\\n+Do not add snapshot tests.  They would duplicate visual states while creating\\n+low-signal approval churn.  The browser story tests are the behavioral and\\n+accessibility contract; visual-regression hosting is a separate decision.\\n+\\n+## Non