ch,tabs}.stories.tsx` | Public visual states plus browser interaction contracts for each initial primitive. |\\n+| `pnpm-lock.yaml` | Resolved, version-aligned package graph. |\\n+\\n+## Chunk 1: Toolchain and host configuration\\n+\\n+### Task 1: Install the minimal, aligned test stack\\n+\\n+**Files:**\\n+- Modify: `apps/web/package.json`\\n+- Modify: `packages/ui/package.json`\\n+- Modify: `pnpm-lock.yaml`\\n+\\n+- [ ] **Step 1: Add current Storybook 10 dependencies to `apps/web`**\\n+\\n+Add the same declared Storybook 10 version range for `storybook`,\\n+`@storybook/nextjs-vite`, `@storybook/addon-docs`, `@storybook/addon-a11y`,\\n+and `@storybook/addon-vitest`. Add matching Vitest 4 and\\n+`@vitest/browser-playwright` development dependencies. Keep all Storybook\\n+packages in one version family. Do not add Chromatic, MCP, links, or a\\n+snapshot/test-runner package.\\n+\\n+- [ ] **Step 2: Add the UI story typecheck dependency and script**\\n+\\n+In `packages/ui/package.json`, add `@typescript/native-preview` from the\\n+workspace catalog and a `typecheck` script:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+\\\"typecheck\\\": \\\"tsgo --noEmit\\\"\\n+```\\n+\\n+The package tsconfig already includes its co-located `.stories.tsx` files.\\n+\\n+- [ ] **Step 3: Preserve default test behavior with explicit scripts**\\n+\\n+Replace the existing web scripts so unit and Storybook projects cannot be\\n+accidentally mixed:\\n+\\n+```json\\n+\\\"test\\\": \\\"vitest run --project unit\\\",\\n+\\\"test:watch\\\": \\\"vitest --project unit\\\",\\n+\\\"storybook\\\": \\\"storybook dev -p 6006\\\",\\n+\\\"storybook:build\\\": \\\"storybook build\\\",\\n+\\\"storybook:test\\\": \\\"vitest run --project storybook\\\",\\n+\\\"storybook:test:watch\\\": \\\"vitest --project storybook\\\"\\n+```\\n+\\n+- [ ] **Step 4: Install and inspect the resolved graph**\\n+\\n+Run: `pnpm install`\\n+\\n+Expected: lockfile resolves one compatible Storybook 10 family and Vitest 4;\\n+no unrelated workspace dependency ch